'''Shōkyū-i''' (正九位) is one of the {{ill|Court Ranks of Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is positioned below {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and above {{ill|Junior Ninth Rank|ja|従九位|1=Junior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the hierarchy.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-Ranks/court-Ranks/</ref>
== Overview ==
Shōkyū-i was established in the early {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} under the {{ill|Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|ja|太政官制|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It was defined by the {{ill|Shokuinryō|ja|職員令|qq=draft|qq=draft}} issued in {{ill|July 1869|ja|1869th year 7月|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and amended on {{ill|August 22, 1869|ja|1869th year 8月22日|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref group="notes" name="enkaku">The Cabinet Records Bureau's "Independent Book: Meiji Official Ranks History, Section on Offices" (National Archives of Japan ref.A07090183000) states it was established on {{ill|July 8 (Lunisolar)|ja|Lunisolar July8日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and revised on {{ill|August 20 (Lunisolar)|ja|Lunisolar August20日|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.</ref><ref name=soutou>[{{NDLDC|787949/168}} 法令全書「明治2nd year 」], National Diet Library.</ref> It corresponded to positions such as officials of the {{ill|Jingikan|ja|神祇官|1=Department of Divinities|blank= (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and scribes of the {{ill|Ministry of Popular Affairs (Meiji period)|ja|民部省 (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
In the honor system established by the {{ill|Joi Jōrei|ja|叙位条例|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Imperial Edict No. 10 of 1887) and the {{ill|Ikai-ryō|ja|位階令|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Imperial Edict No. 325 of 1926), no Rank corresponding to 九位 (Kyū-i) was included.
