== Overview ==
Shōkyū-i was established in the early [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]] under the {{ill|Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|ja|太政官制|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 太政官 (明治時代)}}. It was defined by the {{ill|Shokuinryō|ja|職員令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shokuinryō|qq=}} issued in {{ill|July 1869|ja|1869th year 7月|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 1869|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and amended on {{ill|August 22, 1869|ja|1869th year 8月22日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/August 22, 1869|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.<ref group="notes" name="enkaku">The Cabinet Records Bureau's "Independent Book: Meiji Official Ranks History, Section on Offices" (National Archives of Japan ref.A07090183000) states it was established on {{ill|July 8 (Lunisolar)|ja|Lunisolar July8日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 8 (Lunisolar)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and revised on {{ill|August 20 (Lunisolar)|ja|Lunisolar August20日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/August 20 (Lunisolar)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.</ref><ref name=soutou>[{{NDLDC|787949/168}} 法令全書「明治2nd year 」], National Diet Library.</ref> It corresponded to positions such as officials of the [[:en:Department of Divinities|Department of Divinities]] and scribes of the {{ill|Ministry of Popular Affairs (Meiji period)|ja|民部省 (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ministry of Popular Affairs (Meiji period)|qq=}}.
In the honor system established by the {{ill|Joi Jōrei|ja|叙位条例|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Joi Jōrei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Imperial Edict No. 10 of 1887) and the {{ill|Ikai-ryō|ja|位階令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikai-ryō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 位階}} (Imperial Edict No. 325 of 1926), no Rank corresponding to 九位 (Kyū-i) was included.
